      "content": "The candlelight flickers low, much like the flame of my own weary soul. He is gone, and the silence he left behind is a shroud that smothers me. Everything I built, every hope I harbored... it was all a cruel illusion. I feel as though I am already a ghost, drifting through these cold, hollow halls. There is no light left in this world for a heart so broken. It would be so much simpler, wouldn't it... to just let the darkness take me entirely?",
